<subSubSection id="C365CEF67707FFA24EA959BDFF5BAF6E" lastPageId="101" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC09D7D7707FFA24EA959BDFF5BAF6E" blockId="100.[151,1437,1707,2022]" lastBlockId="101.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="101" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis id="B90B416F7707FFA34EA959BDFE94A9ED" bold="true" box="[199,315,1924,1950]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE7707FFA34F2B59BAFDD5A9EE" authorityName="Werding" authorityYear="1978" box="[325,634,1923,1949]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magdalenensis">
<emphasis id="B90B416F7707FFA34F2B59BAFDD5A9EE" box="[325,634,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Petrolisthes magdalenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a scarcely recorded western Atlantic species closely related to the eastern Pacific 
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE7707FFA34F2D5991FE0FA9B2" baseAuthorityName="Glassell" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[323,416,1959,1985]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lewisi">
<emphasis id="B90B416F7707FFA34F2D5991FE0FA9B2" box="[323,416,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lewisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the two species being in sister position (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C7707FFA34D1F5991FC41A9B1" author="Gore, R. H." box="[881,1006,1960,1986]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref72204" refString="Gore, R. H. (1982) Porcellanid crabs from the coasts of Mexico and Central America (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 363, 1 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.363" type="journal article" year="1982">Gore 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C7707FFA34D94599EFB5EA9B1" author="Rodriguez, I. T. &amp; Hernandez, G. &amp; Felder, D. L." box="[1018,1265,1959,1986]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="544 - 582" refId="ref76152" refString="Rodriguez, I. T., Hernandez, G. &amp; Felder, D. L. (2005) Review of the western Atlantic Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura) with new records, systematic observations, and comments on biogeography. Caribbean Journal of Science, 41 (3), 544 - 582." type="journal article" year="2005">
Rodríguez 
<emphasis id="B90B416F7707FFA34A185991FB00A9B2" box="[1142,1199,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
, 2006; see also 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C7707FFA34EF959F2FE30A995" author="Werding, B. &amp; Hiller, A." box="[151,415,1995,2022]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="1185 - 1190" refId="ref77650" refString="Werding, B. &amp; Hiller, A. (2005) A new porcellanid species from the Caribbean Sea, with a discussion on the American &quot; Petrolisthes lewisi - group &quot; (Decapoda, Anomura, Porcellanidae). Crustaceana, 78 (10), 1185 - 1190. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854005775903582" type="journal article" year="2005">Werding &amp; Hiller 2005</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEEE08C7707FFA34C2459F2FD51A995" author="Werding, B." box="[586,766,1995,2022]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="173 - 214" refId="ref77184" refString="Werding, B. (1977) Los porcelanidos (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae) de la region de Santa Marta, Colombia. Anales del Instituto de Investigaciones Marinas de Punta Betin, 9, 173 - 214. https: // doi. org / 10.25268 / bimc. invemar. 1977.9.0.527" type="journal article" year="1977">Werding (1977)</bibRefCitation>
, the species has a very characteristic colouration: the colour of the carapace and P1 varies from light grey to yellowish, frequently with brownish spots; the P2–P4 are brown, darker distally; and the P1 is brownish distally. A specimen from Utila, 
<collectingCountry id="F368DDED7706FFA24DD55E82FB84AEA6" box="[955,1067,187,213]" name="Honduras" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Honduras</collectingCountry>
, tentatively identified by us as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7FE6FE7706FFA24BE65E82FE92AE8A" authorityName="Werding" authorityYear="1978" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magdalenensis">
<emphasis id="B90B416F7706FFA24BE65E82FE92AE8A" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">P. magdalenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on its overall morphology and colouration, is illustrated (
<figureCitation id="134481F87706FFA24A7C5EE6FBCBAE89" box="[1042,1124,223,250]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="101.[151,250,924,948]" captionTargetBox="[271,1316,309,901]" captionTargetId="figure-79@101.[271,1316,309,901]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURE 62. Petrolisthes magdalenensis Werding, 1978: extra-limital specimen, possibly male (cl cw indet.), from Utila, Honduras (not deposited), dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532363/files/figure.png" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
) to ease the species’ identification.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
